{
  "children": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "On the Efficiency of Persistent Data Structures"
        }
      ],
      "level": 1,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Abstract"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "We present a comprehensive analysis of persistent data structures and their amortized time complexity. Our results show that path copying combined with lazy evaluation achieves "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "O(\\log n)"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " amortized time for most operations. We introduce a novel technique for reducing the constant factor in persistent balanced trees."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Introduction"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Persistent data structures preserve previous versions of themselves when modified"
        },
        {
          "label": "driscoll1989",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": ". Unlike ephemeral data structures, which support only a single version, persistent structures maintain a version history."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "This property is essential for:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "items": [
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Functional programming languages"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Version control systems"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Database transaction logs"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "children": [
            {
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "Undo/redo mechanisms"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "unordered_list"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Background"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Persistence Levels"
        }
      ],
      "level": 3,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "items": [
        {
          "definitions": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Any version can be queried or updated"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "term": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Full persistence"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "definitions": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Any version can be queried, only the latest updated"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "term": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Partial persistence"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "definitions": [
            [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "value": "Versions can be combined (merged)"
              }
            ]
          ],
          "term": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "value": "Confluent persistence"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
      "type": "definition_list"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Related Work"
        }
      ],
      "level": 3,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Driscoll et al."
        },
        {
          "label": "driscoll1989",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " introduced the fat node and path copying techniques. Okasaki"
        },
        {
          "label": "okasaki1998",
          "type": "footnote_ref"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " developed purely functional approaches using lazy evaluation."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Our Approach"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "We define the cost of an operation on version "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "v"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " as:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "body": "C(v) = T_{access}(v) + T_{copy}(v) + T_{rebalance}(v)",
      "type": "math_block"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Where "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "T_{access}"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " is the time to locate the node, "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "T_{copy}"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " is the path copying cost, and "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "T_{rebalance}"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " is the structural adjustment cost."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Amortized Analysis"
        }
      ],
      "level": 3,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Using the potential method, we assign a potential "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "\\Phi"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " to each version:"
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "body": "\\hat{c}_i = c_i + \\Phi_i - \\Phi_{i-1}",
      "type": "math_block"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "The amortized cost "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "\\hat{c}_i"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " accounts for both the actual cost "
        },
        {
          "type": "inline_math",
          "value": "c_i"
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": " and the change in potential."
        }
      ],
      "type": "paragraph"
    },
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "value": "Results"
        }
      ],
      "level": 2,
      "type": "heading"
    },
    {
